            <title>[JCR-2765] JCR-SQL2 : no count when WHERE clause is provided</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2765</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>whenever you provide a where-clause to a sql2 select, jcr/jackrabbit does not provide the hit count.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
E.g.:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;select * from [nt:unstructured]&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;order by [jcr:score]&lt;br/&gt;
returns the hit count (query.execute().getRows().getSize()), &lt;br/&gt;
whereas&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;select * from [nt:unstructured]&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;where entity = &amp;quot;customer&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;order by [jcr:score]&lt;br/&gt;
doesn&amp;#39;t.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
