                    <comment id="12923566" author="alexander.klimetschek" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 19:51:58 +0100"  >This is not a blocker - maybe for your requirements, but not for Jackrabbit. A blocker would be that jackrabbit does not start, no nodes/properties could be read etc.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Since getSize() can return -1 by definition (and the order by trick to force getSize() have the hit count returned is just a &amp;quot;trick&amp;quot;), this is actually an improvement. Manually counting through the iterator is the way to go without the trick.</comment>
                    <comment id="12923763" author="clemensdev" created="Fri, 22 Oct 2010 06:41:14 +0100"  >I agree that this is not a &amp;quot;Blocker&amp;quot;, but manually counting through an iterator, just to get the count, is not really an option</comment>
